No one is sure who ranked the dads but it definitely happened. Most dads feel they were not ranked highly enough and they wonder if the rankings will change the next day. All the dads now have a chip on their shoulder and feel they need to step up their game. 

Dads start getting home from work on time. They stop stopping at the bars. They stop making excuses. There are more dads wanting to coach teams than there are teams.  After a week the rankings change and even more dads take notice. 
There are now more dads making family dinners, helping with homework, taking the little league team to practice, and even running in marath
ons! The moms have never been so happy. They now have true teammates in the dads. The kids have never been so happy either because they have guidance and love from their dads. 

Soon every mom gets a dad a coffee mug. The dads are kept honest by these mugs. They know if they start slacking, the mug will rank them lowly.   They are forced to be the best dads they can be.
